{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17600651","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17600651"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:06:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:06:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15626"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15626","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15626"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.24,0,0.55,0.14,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8317"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66740"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8317"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15626"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52195"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3320"},{"type":"tags","id":"3521"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5884"},{"type":"tags","id":"7004"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20067"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20070"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22304"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66740","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66740"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents with galactorrhoea, irregular menstrual periods, and a 5 mm pituitary adenoma on magnetic resonance imaging (Image). Her serum prolactin level is 85 \u00b5g/L (4-23).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications is most appropriate as first-line treatment?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Metoclopramide","Lithium","Cabergoline","Phenothiazines","Ranitidine"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical features and elevated prolactin level are consistent with a prolactin-secreting pituitary adenoma (prolactinoma). \u003Cstrong\u003ECabergoline\u003C/strong\u003E is a dopamine agonist that suppresses prolactin secretion and is the first-line medical treatment for prolactinomas.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe other options actually increase prolactin levels:\u003C/p\u003E    \u003Cul\u003E    \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetoclopramide\u003C/strong\u003E is a dopamine antagonist that increases prolactin secretion\u003C/li\u003E    \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELithium\u003C/strong\u003E interferes with dopamine signalling and can raise prolactin levels\u003C/li\u003E    \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhenothiazines\u003C/strong\u003E are dopamine antagonists that increase prolactin secretion\u003C/li\u003E    \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERanitidine\u003C/strong\u003E and other histamine-2 receptor antagonists can cause mild hyperprolactinaemia\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Cabergoline is a dopamine agonist and first-line treatment for prolactinomas","Dopamine normally inhibits prolactin secretion from the anterior pituitary","Medications that block dopamine can increase prolactin levels"],"references":["Fukuhara N, Nishiyama M, Iwasaki Y. Update in Pathogenesis, Diagnosis, and Therapy of Prolactinoma. Cancers (Basel). 2022 Jul 24;14(15):3604. doi: 10.3390/cancers14153604. PMID: 35892862; PMCID: PMC9331865","Dai C, Kang J, Liu X, Yao Y, Wang H, Wang R. How to Classify and Define Pituitary Tumors: Recent Advances and Current Controversies. Front Endocrinol (Lausanne). 2021 Mar 17;12:604644. doi: 10.3389/fendo.2021.604644. PMID: 33815274; PMCID: PMC8010908","Lenders NF, Earls PE, Inder WJ, McCormack AI. The evolution in pituitary tumour classification: a clinical perspective. Endocr Oncol. 2023 Apr 21;3(1):e220079. doi: 10.1530/EO-22-0079. PMID: 37434652; PMCID: PMC10305559","Yatavelli RKR, Bhusal K. Prolactinoma. [Updated 2023 Jul 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459347/","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes. Oxford University Press, USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52195"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15626"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21279"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21279","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21279"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/fECxvgmX2A0ZJHo4yZ1zP63qN5RzRT.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/fECxvgmX2A0ZJHo4yZ1zP63qN5RzRT.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":446,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52195","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52195"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T20:44:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T20:45:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8317"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66740"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science"